Package net.dean.jraw.paginators

Contains classes used to iterate through models

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    RedditIterable<T extends Thing>  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CommentStream
    A Paginator geared towards viewing the comments on a subreddit.
    CompoundSubredditPaginator
    Provides a way to iterate through multiple subreddits without using multireddits.
    DuplicatesPaginator
    Iterates through duplicates of a submission
    GenericPaginator<T extends Thing>
    This class provides a template for Paginators that use only a "where" attribute, such as /user/username/{where}.
    GenericUserRecordPaginator
    This class provides a bridge between GenericPaginator and concrete subclasses of GenericPaginator<UserRecord> by providing an implementation of GenericUserRecordPaginator.parseListing(RestResponse) suitable for creating Listing<UserRecord> objects.
    ImportantUserPaginator
    This class provides the ability to paginate over a user's friends and blocked users
    InboxPaginator
    Provides a way to iterate over a user's inbox
    LiveThreadPaginator
    Provides a way to iterate through the updates in a live thread.
    ModeratorPaginator
    This class provides a way to iterate over submissions and comments relevant to moderators, such as those reported and marked as spam.
    ModLogPaginator
    This class allows the iteration of the log of moderation actions on a particular subreddit
    MultiHubPaginator
    This is specially designed to iterate /r/multihub and pick out information about multireddits submitted there.
    MultiHubPaginator.MultiRedditId
    This class is a "hacky" way to return a MultiReddit's name and owner without actually having to send any HTTP requests.
    MultiRedditPaginator
    Iterates through the posts in a multireddit.
    Paginator<T extends Thing>
    Provides the ability to iterate through data provided by the Reddit API.
    RelatedPaginator
    Iterates through submissions related to a given one
    SpecificPaginator
    This class provides a way to iterate through a list of Submissions by their names.
    SubmissionSearchPaginator
    This class allows access to Reddit's search functionality.
    SubredditPaginator
    This class is used to paginate through the front page or a subreddit with different time periods or sortings.
    SubredditSearchPaginator
    This class provides a way to search for subreddits by both name and description
    SubredditStream
    This paginator will iterate through subreddits based on certain criteria.
    UserContributionPaginator
    This class is used to paginate through user posts or comments via /user/{username}/{where}.json
    UserRecordPaginator
    This class provides a way to iterate over the users that have been banned, marked as contributors, etc.
    UserSubredditsPaginator
    This paginator provides a way to iterate through the logged-in user's subreddits they interact with, whether that be through being a contributor of, a moderator of, or are subscribed to
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description

    Represents how the reddit API chooses what it returns in a Paginator
    SubmissionSearchPaginator.SearchSort
    How the search results can be sorted
